# Soulspedia — Cursor Rules

## Project
Dark Fantasy lore archive (Dark Souls I/II/III, expanding to Elden Ring).
Goal: atmospheric, scholarly, cinematic UX. Never generic or bouncy.
Next.js 16 App Router · React 19 · TypeScript · Supabase · Tailwind CSS v4.
Always use `@/` alias for imports.

---

## Skills — Read Before Acting

These skill files contain the detailed rules for each domain.
**Always read the relevant skill before writing code in that area.**

| When you are working on... | Read this skill |
|---|---|
| Any animation, transition, or motion effect | `.cursor/skills/framer-motion-fromsoftware.md` |
| Pages, layouts, images, routing, data fetching | `.cursor/skills/nextjs-app-router.md` |
| Tailwind classes, colors, effects, responsive | `.cursor/skills/tailwind-dark-ui.md` |
| Any UI component, section, or visual design | `.cursor/skills/frontend-design-soulspedia.md` |

---

## Workflow (Álvaro's Method)
- New features or complex fixes: always start with a `@plan` before writing code.
- Work section-by-section. Never refactor a whole page in one step.
- If context is missing, ask for a URL or search before assuming.
- Use Supabase MCP if available; otherwise use `@/lib/supabase.ts`.
- Before running any terminal command or file system operation 
  (searching, reading, listing files), explain in one line what 
  it does and why.
---

## Key Files
- `@/lib/motion/fromSoftware.ts` — all animation timing/easing presets
- `@/lib/supabase.ts` — Supabase client
- `@/components/motion/Reveal.tsx` — scroll reveal wrapper
- `@/components/game/GameHubLanding.client.tsx` — reusable game hub base
- `@/app/globals.css` — CSS variables, @font-face, .page-shell

---

## Non-Negotiable Rules
1. Background is always `#050505`, never `#000`.
2. All bg images use `next/image` with opacity + gradient overlays. Never CSS `background-image`.
3. Minimum 0.85s for page-level animations. Read the animation skill for all timing values.
4. `font-optimus` is always `uppercase`. No exceptions.
5. No `spring`, `bounce`, or `elastic` in any animation.
6. `useReducedMotion()` in every animated component. Not optional.
7. Borders are always semi-transparent (`white/5` to `white/25`). No opaque borders.
8. Never hardcode horizontal margins — use `.page-shell` or `--page-margin-x`.
